messages.content:
It's a bundle set.It's from the company Promate Philippines. My sister's  friend said to get daw the "120 & 30w solar
panel bundle" that's around 12k+.
I'm in contact na with the warehouse here in Manila. They can give it for PHP10,800.00 for 30pcs minimum.
Promate 120 is battery operated you can charge via ac socket and car charger, kapag brown out pwede din sa solar panel foldable 30watts. Also it has built in LED lights. So you can charge phones and small appliances depending on wattage.

Right now we are finding a way to transport these and other donations from Manila to Cebu since commercial airlines won't allow gensets and the like for check in. While we are working on that, we also trying to gather orders of 30 units. For personal use and/ or donations.
But if we don't reach the minimum, we still plan to purchase even if not the discounted rate.

Initially wanted to get this for my family. But I have friends now wanting to purchase also for their families. My sister also wants to donate sets to those in Olango island and other places.
